abstract: The 1980 census will be the first to have pretested its words. ("Pretested" is silly, as is "prerecorded"; kill the redundant "pre.") The phrasing of the questionnaire was tested four years ago in a National Content Test on 28,000 households to discover what would be most understandable and inoffensive.
